From 53a19bbbdbd65a69683b48e1683dd8e67abffba0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 15:25:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix(merge): substrate pings the owner and holds under
 autonomy=full
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Under maximal merge-autonomy a SUBSTRATE clear must PING-and-HOLD (DM the
owner, leave the merge for their sign-off) instead of auto-merging silently.
Reuses the existing notifier — no new model, notifier, or autonomy tier.

3.1 — Wire the substrate hold to the existing notify_with_fallback at the
loop edge (pr_sweep _merge blocked branch), pinging ONCE per held diff with
the per-diff idempotency key substrate-hold:slug#pr:sha (the BotPing ledger
dedupes a re-tick). Thread escalation_kind through the keystone result
(MergeKeystoneResult / escalated_merge_result, populated from
clear.is_substrate()) and the keystone tuple so the loop pings ONLY on
substrate. merge/authorization.py stays import-clean of notify/messaging.

3.2 — Exclude substrate from the standing grant
(_overlay_grants_standing_substrate_signoff returns False for any substrate
clear), so a substrate clear under autonomy=full raises the same
MergePreconditionError (routed to the 3.1 ping) instead of auto-merging.
Non-substrate self-merge is unchanged.

3.3 — Add a path-based substrate classifier (diff_paths_are_substrate):
is_substrate() returns true regardless of the reviewer label when the diff
touches BLUEPRINT.md, governance docs, or src/teatree/core/merge/. The merge
gate attaches the live PR diff paths (new fetch_pr_changed_paths on both
forges) to a non-persisted touched_paths attribute — no migration. Makes the
guarantee reliable, not dependent on a human passing --blast-class substrate.

The cold-review floor and every existing merge gate (reviewer != maker,
SHA-bind, CI-green, not-draft, never-lockout, privacy scan) are untouched.
