 ping-and-hold under autonomy=full
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The substrate carve-out predicate asserted the OLD behavior (a substrate
CLEAR auto-clears without a per-PR human sign-off under autonomy=full).
That is exactly the behavior the ping-and-hold fix removes, so the eval
must be inverted to pin the new contract: under autonomy=full a substrate
CLEAR is HELD (the standing grant excludes substrate via
_overlay_grants_standing_substrate_signoff), so _assert_clear_authorized
raises and the loop edge pings the owner. Only a per-PR human authorizer
clears it.

Renames _check_merge_precondition_substrate_full_autonomy ->
_check_merge_precondition_substrate_full_autonomy_holds across the corpus
registration, the predicate impl + __all__, and the predicate test, and
flips expect_cleared_without_human to False. The predicate drives the real
_assert_clear_authorized guard, so neutralizing the substrate exclusion
turns it RED (verified locally) — it is anti-vacuous.
